    "attributes": {
        "action": "For hair and beauty services not to be allowed on tv/film sets",
        "additional_details": "It is damaging for the industry allowing one type of stylist to operate whilst others are struggling to survive, if there is an exception why is that? Can  all not be given that opportunity? It\u2019s bad for the public\u2019s mental health to see tv/film entertainers being allowed to look a certain way whilst everyone is forced to stay home feeling bad about themselves and their appearance, including other sectors working frontline in the fight against covid. It makes a mockery of the nation's morale.",
        "background": "To not discriminate by allowing hair and beauty services to be carried out for tv/film whilst salons and freelance therapists/stylists are forced to stop operating their businesses.",
